item.title: Vulnhub Darknet1.0 write up
item.description: Darknet 1.0 by q3rv0 isn’t easy… for me anyway. With some help and lots of reading I did however get to the bottom of it. Here’s my journey Stage 1 First things first: scan the target root@kali:~# nmap -sV -p- 192.168.56.106 Starting Nmap 6.47 ( http://nmap.org ) at 2015-06-03 12:57 BST Nmap scan report for darknet.com (192.168.56.106) Host is up (0.00017s latency). Not shown: 65532 closed ports PORT STATE SERVICE VERSION 80/tcp open http Apache httpd 2.2.22 ((Debian)) 111/tcp open rpcbind 2-4 (RPC #100000) 57664/tcp open status 1 (RPC #100024) MAC Address: 08:00:27:E5:9F:EC (Cadmus Computer Systems) Service detection performed.
